{
  "stem": "812.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "I was very fortunate that I stayed with my mother, and my brother was able to stay with my father.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "Men and women were separated.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "We were fortunate in that we were able to get glimpses of one another every so often.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 76,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Our bunks were made up of three or four slats, wooden slats, some straw as a mattress, and one thin blanket.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 77,
      "text": "And that was for the two of us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "That was our-- those were our quarters.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We-- our food consisted of a pat of butter, a slice of bread a day.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And then we would get, every once in a while, a turnip soup with some gristle in it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "The bread and the butter was later cut back to just once a week, and that was given to us only if our quarters were in order, if our blanket was straightened.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "There was constant inspection, constant fear that things might not be right, might not be the way it suits the Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "So it always had to be on guard to make sure that our quarters were in order.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "We would give each other, on our birthdays, the slice of bread that we would have saved-- that we saved from previous weeks.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "And not that we had a calendar there, but we had an approximate idea as to what the calendar months were.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I remember at one point seeing a cart with what I thought was firewood for the one small oven that we had in our barrack.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "And actually, what I saw being hauled away were naked bodies, one stacked on top of the other.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "And it was sights like this, the constant death and filth and horror that we lived with.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
